---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Why Every Tradie in NZ Needs a Website in 2026 — SiteGenius" description="Plumbers, electricians, builders, painters — if you're a tradie in NZ without a website, you're losing jobs to the competition. Here's why and what to do about it.">
  <article class="pt-32 pb-24">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Article Header -->
      <header class="mb-16 text-center">
        <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-4 block">Trades & Services</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-8 leading-tight">
          Why Every Tradie in NZ Needs a <span class="gradient-text">Website</span> in 2026
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-muted-200">
          Word of mouth is gold — but the blokes who show up on Google are getting the jobs you never even hear about.
        </p>
      </header>

      <!-- Hero Image -->
      <div class="mb-16 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/[0.06]">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1504307651254-35680f356dfd?w=1200&h=600&fit=crop" alt="Tradie working on a construction site in New Zealand" class="w-full h-64 md:h-80 object-cover" loading="lazy" />
      </div>

      <!-- Article Content -->
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-invert max-w-none">
        <div class="glass p-8 mb-12 rounded-3xl border-neon-cyan/20">
          <p class="text-lg font-medium text-space-800 leading-relaxed m-0 text-muted-100">
            Look, we get it. You're flat out. Between quoting jobs, wrangling suppliers, and actually doing the mahi, building a website is about as appealing as a rainy Monday on a roofing job. But here's the thing — your competitors have one, and they're picking up the customers who should be calling you. Let's break down why a website is no longer optional for tradies in Aotearoa.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">The "Plumber Near Me" Effect</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Think about the last time you needed something done around the house. Chances are, you grabbed your phone and Googled it. Your customers are doing the exact same thing. Searches like "plumber near me," "electrician Auckland," and "builder Christchurch" have gone through the roof in the last few years.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Here's how it works: when someone searches "plumber near me" on their phone, Google shows them a map with three local businesses (the "Local Pack"), followed by regular search results. If you don't have a website and a <a href="/blog/google-business-profile-nz" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">Google Business Profile</a>, you're invisible. It's that simple.
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8 text-muted-200">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>76% of people</strong> who search for something local on their phone visit a business within 24 hours.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>28% of those searches</strong> result in a purchase or booking.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>"Near me" searches</strong> have grown by over 500% in the last five years across NZ.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">"But I Get All My Work From Word of Mouth"</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Yeah nah, we hear this one a lot. And word of mouth is brilliant — no argument there. But here's what actually happens: someone recommends you, and the first thing the customer does is Google your name. If nothing comes up, or all they find is a dodgy Facebook page with no recent posts, they start to wonder if you're legit.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          A professional website backs up every referral. It tells people: "This person is established, trustworthy, and does quality work." Even a simple site with your services, some photos of your work, and a phone number makes a massive difference.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Plus, word of mouth only reaches so far. A website reaches everyone in your area, 24/7 — even when you're on the tools or having a cold one after work.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">What Pages Does a Tradie Website Actually Need?</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Good news — a tradie website doesn't need to be complicated. You don't need 50 pages or fancy animations. Here's what actually matters:
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 my-10 not-prose">
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-3">Home Page</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm">Who you are, what you do, where you work, and how to contact you. That's it. Make it dead simple. Include your phone number front and centre — tradies' customers want to call, not fill in forms.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neon-purple mb-3">Services Page</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm">List every service you offer. Don't just say "plumbing" — say "hot water cylinder installation," "blocked drain clearing," "bathroom renovations." Each specific service helps you show up for more Google searches.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-emerald-500 mb-3">About Page</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm">People hire people, not businesses. Share a bit about yourself — how long you've been in the trade, your qualifications, what areas you cover. A friendly photo goes a long way.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-500 mb-3">Gallery / Portfolio</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm">Before-and-after photos are absolute gold. Nothing builds trust faster than seeing your actual work. Snap a quick photo before you finish each job — your future self will thank you.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neon-cyan mb-3">Testimonials</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm">Got happy customers? Ask them for a quick review and stick it on your site. Even three or four good testimonials can be the difference between someone calling you or the other guy.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="glass-hover p-6 rounded-2xl">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-neon-purple mb-3">Contact Page</h3>
            <p class="text-muted-200 text-sm">Phone number, email, a simple contact form, and the areas you cover. Make it ridiculously easy for people to get in touch. Include your hours — customers appreciate knowing when they can reach you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">How Tradies in Different Trades Benefit</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Whether you're a sparky, a chippy, or a painter, the benefits are the same — but the specifics differ a bit. Here's how a website works for different trades:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-8 text-muted-200">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Plumbers:</strong> Emergency plumbing searches peak at night and on weekends — exactly when you can't answer the phone. A website with a contact form captures those leads while you sleep. Target keywords like "emergency plumber [your city]."</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Electricians:</strong> Homeowners want to see qualifications and registrations before letting someone touch their wiring. Display your electrical registration number prominently. Target "registered electrician [your area]."</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Builders:</strong> Large projects mean customers do serious research. A portfolio of completed builds with photos and details can win you five-figure contracts. Target "house builder" or "renovation builder" + your region.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Painters:</strong> Before-and-after photos are your secret weapon. Nothing shows value like a visual transformation. Target "house painter [your city]" and "commercial painter [your region]."</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-neon-cyan font-bold mt-1">→</span>
            <span><strong>Landscapers:</strong> Gallery pages work brilliantly for landscapers. Show off those outdoor living areas and garden transformations. Target "landscaper near me" and "garden design [your city]."</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">"I Don't Have Time to Maintain a Website"</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Fair call. You're not sitting behind a desk — you're on-site, covered in dust or up to your elbows in pipes. That's exactly why a subscription website service like <a href="/services" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">SiteGenius</a> exists.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          We build and maintain your website for you. Need to add a new service? Flick us a text. Got some new photos of a job you're proud of? Send them through and we'll get them up. You focus on what you're good at — the actual trade work — and we'll handle the website.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Our plans start from just $79/month, which includes the design, hosting, SSL, and ongoing updates. That's less than the cost of a single no-show job. Check out our <a href="/pricing" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">pricing</a> for the full breakdown.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">Don't Forget Your Google Business Profile</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          A website and a Google Business Profile work together like a hammer and nails. Your GBP gets you on Google Maps and in the Local Pack, while your website gives customers the detail they need to pick up the phone. We've written a full guide on <a href="/blog/google-business-profile-nz" class="text-neon-cyan hover:underline">setting up your Google Business Profile in NZ</a> — it's free and takes about 20 minutes.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6 text-space-900">The Bottom Line</h2>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-6">
          Every day without a website is a day you're losing potential work to the tradies who do have one. It doesn't need to be flash — it just needs to exist, look professional, and make it easy for people to contact you. In 2026, a website isn't a "nice to have" for tradies — it's as essential as your ute and your tools.
        </p>
        <p class="text-muted-200 mb-10">
          The best part? You don't have to build it yourself. That's literally our job.
        </p>

        <!-- CTA Inside Blog -->
        <div class="mt-16 p-10 bg-gradient-to-r from-neon-cyan/10 to-neon-purple/10 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 text-center text-space-900">
          <h3 class="text-3xl font-black mb-4 text-muted-100">Get a Tradie Website From $79/mo</h3>
          <p class="text-lg text-muted-200 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">We'll build and maintain your website so you can focus on the tools. Custom design, hosting, and support included — no upfront costs.</p>
          <a href="/get-a-quote" class="btn-primary">Get Your Free Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
